Difference in apical F between the OM and SRA. Positive values indicate higher F in the OM.

SSB comparison between the OM and SRA.

Difference in spawning biomass (SSB), relative to SSB0, between the OM and SRA, calculated as \((SSB^{OM}_y - SSB^{SRA}_y)/SSB^{OM}_0\). Positive values indicate higher SSB in the OM.

Recruitment comparison between the OM and SRA.

Difference in recruitment (relative to R0) between the OM and SRA, calculated as \((R^{OM}_y - R^{SRA}_y)/R^{OM}_0\). Positive values indicate higher recruitment in the OM.

Comparison of total removals between the OM and SRA.

Difference in annual catch (relative to observed), calculated as \(C^{OM}_y/C^{obs}_y - 1\). Positive values indicate higher catch in the OM. Catch in the OM is the total removals (both landings and discards).
